no-multi-str.description:
Description

This rule is aimed at preventing the use of multiline strings.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-multi-str: "error"*/

const x = "some very \
long text";

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-multi-str: "error"*/

const x = "some very long text";

const y = "some very " +
        "long text";
